  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the major aspects covered under ISO/TS 16949 Audit?",
  "response": "ISO/TS 16949 is a technical specification that outlines the requirements for a quality management system (QMS) specifically for the automotive industry. It incorporates the principles of ISO 9001 while adding additional automotive-specific requirements. A typical ISO/TS 16949 audit covers several major aspects, including:\n\n1. **Quality Management System Documentation**:\n   - Review of the quality manual, policies, and procedures.\n   - Assessment of document control processes and record-keeping.\n\n2. **Management Responsibility**:\n   - Evaluation of top management's commitment to the QMS.\n   - Review of quality objectives, planning, and communication of the importance of the QMS.\n\n3. **Resource Management**:\n   - Assessment of human resources, including training, competence, and awareness.\n   - Evaluation of infrastructure and work environment to ensure they are suitable for achieving product conformity.\n\n4. **Product Realization**:\n   - Examination of planning processes for product realization.\n   - Review of design and development, including design verification and validation activities.\n   - Evaluation of supplier management, purchasing processes, and receipt inspection.\n   - Assessment of production and service provision processes, including process control and monitoring.\n\n5. **Measurement, Analysis, and Improvement**:\n   - Review of processes for monitoring and measuring product quality.\n   - Assessment of analysis of data and monitoring of customer satisfaction.\n   - Evaluation of corrective and preventive actions to address non-conformities.\n   - Examination of continuous improvement initiatives, including the use of quality tools and techniques.\n\n6. **Compliance with Regulatory and Customer Requirements**:\n   - Assessment of adherence to relevant automotive regulatory standards and customer-specific requirements.\n\n7. **Risk Management**:\n   - Evaluation of risk assessment processes and mitigation strategies related to product quality and safety.\n\n8. **Internal Audits**:\n   - Review of internal audit processes and effectiveness.\n   - Assessment of audit planning, execution, and corrective actions.\n\n9. **Supply Chain Management**:\n   - Evaluation of supplier qualification and performance monitoring systems.\n   - Examination of processes for managing supplier-related risks and quality.\n\n10. **Training and Competency**:\n    - Assessment of training programs to ensure personnel are competent to perform their tasks effectively.\n\nAn audit will involve interviews, document reviews, and site inspections, and may also include follow-up on previous audit findings to ensure continual compliance and improvement.",
